# Article 2: 5 Products Cause 31% of All Deaths Worldwide

## Translated Title
5 Products Cause 31% of All Deaths Worldwide

## Category
P0 - Public Health, Corporate Influence, Chronic Disease Prevention

## Source Studies
1. **New England Journal of Medicine** (March 25, 2026) - Corporate Vectors of Chronic Disease
2. **The Lancet** (2019) - GBD 2017 Dietary Risks

## Key Findings

### Five Deadly Product Categories
- **Fossil fuels:** 8.1 million deaths/year
- **Tobacco:** 7.2 million deaths/year
- **Ultra-processed foods:** 2.3 million deaths/year
- **Industrial chemicals:** 1.8 million deaths/year
- **Alcohol:** 1.8 million deaths/year
- **Total: 21.2 million deaths (31% of global mortality)**

### Chronic Disease Burden
- Chronic diseases cause 74% of deaths globally
- 90% of deaths in developed countries
- Unhealthy diet causes >11 million additional deaths annually

### Corporate Tactics (Documented)
- Same playbook across industries: tobacco, sugar, food, chemicals, pharmaceuticals, fossil fuels
- Evidence hidden for decades
- Regulations delayed through lobbying
- Responsibility shifted to individuals
- 80% of premature deaths preventable through lifestyle interventions

